ck end and provides a simple mechanism for plugging in your custom or third-party provided cloud connectors."}],"references":{"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes":{"images":[{"type":"icon","identifier":"WWDCNotes.png"}],"type":"topic","kind":"symbol","role":"collection","title":"WWDC Notes","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Session notes shared by the community for the community."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes"},"WWDC17.jpeg":{"type":"image","alt":null,"identifier":"WWDC17.jpeg","variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC17.jpeg"}]},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC17":{"images":[{"type":"icon","identifier":"WWDC17-Icon.png"},{"type":"card","identifier":"WWDC17.jpeg"}],"type":"topic","kind":"article","role":"collectionGroup","title":"WWDC17","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc17","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Xcode 9, Swift 4.0, iOS 11, macOS 10.13 (High Sierra), tvOS 11, watchOS 4."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"New APIs: "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Core NFC"},{"type":"text","text":" and more."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC17"},"https://wwdcnotes.com/documentation/wwdcnotes/contributing":{"type":"link","identifier":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing","title":"Learn More…","url":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Learn More…"}]},"WWDCNotes.png":{"type":"image","identifier":"WWDCNotes.png","alt":null,"variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDCNotes.png","traits":["1x","light"]}]},"https://nonstrict.eu/wwdcindex/wwdc2017/239/":{"type":"download","checksum":null,"url":"https:\/\/nonstrict.eu\/wwdcindex\/wwdc2017\/239\/","identifier":"https:\/\/nonstrict.eu\/wwdcindex\/wwdc2017\/239\/"},"WWDC17-Icon.png":{"type":"image","identifier":"WWDC17-Icon.png","alt":null,"variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC17-Icon.png","traits":["1x","light"]}]},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC17-232-Whats-New-in-CareKit-and-ResearchKit":{"url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc17-232-whats-new-in-carekit-and-researchkit","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC17-232-Whats-New-in-CareKit-and-ResearchKit","role":"sampleCode","kind":"article","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Whether you’re a medical researcher or a care provider, the CareKit and ResearchKit open source projects are designed to be the quickest path to delivering a customized iOS app to your candidates or patients. These frameworks are constantly gaining features and functionality from both Apple and the community. Discover the latest active-tasks, care modules, and tools designed to allow medical professionals the ability prototype their own care app."}],"title":"What’s New in CareKit and ResearchKit","type":"topic"}}}